   <h3 class="sectionHead"><span class="titlemark">1.1   </span> <a id="x1-180002.2"></a>UPOD -- From Mr. Brown</h3>
<!--l. 144--><p class="noindent" >Good interfaces vs. bad interfaces. Bad interfaces stick with you . Mr. Brown remembers a command line
software which upon typing quit the software told you to type exit. This was obviously a poor design
choice. Mr. Brown also talks about using content which is standardized. For instance making links blue
and underlined became the standard and it is what we are now used to. Using standardized objects makes
the page easier for users to navigate and stops the user from having to learn anything form using the page.
